NODE_ENV=development
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=3000
LOG_LEVEL=info

# Midtrans (QRIS payments). Leave unset locally to disable the /v1/payments/* routes
# (they will respond 503 payments_unavailable). In CI/staging, source the sandbox
# server key from secrets, never commit it.
# MIDTRANS_SERVER_KEY=SB-Mid-server-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
MIDTRANS_ENVIRONMENT=sandbox

# BullMQ broker for the worker process group. Leave unset locally to skip the
# Redis bootstrap (the worker logs and idles instead). For staging/production,
# Fly secrets bind a per-environment Upstash URL — see docs/CI-CD.md §3.10.
# REDIS_URL=redis://default:password@localhost:6379

# Sentry runtime init (KASA-143). Leave unset locally so dev / CI / staging
# without a DSN run silent. Production and staging bind the project DSN as a
# Fly secret. SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT separates `production` from `staging` /
# `preview` events even though NODE_ENV stays `production` on every Fly tier
# — see apps/api/fly.toml. KASSA_API_VERSION (set by CD) drives the Sentry
# release tag (`kassa-api@<sha12>`); see docs/CI-CD.md §3.5b.
# SENTRY_DSN=https://<key>@<org>.ingest.sentry.io/<project>
# SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=development

# OpenTelemetry trace export (KASA-284). Leave unset locally — `sale.submit`
# and `eod.close` spans then run against the OTEL API's NoOp tracer (no
# overhead, no exports) and the API does not crash on boot. Production sets
# this to the OTLP/HTTP collector URL; `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME` defaults to
# `kassa-api` when unset. See docs/ARCHITECTURE.md §5.5 for the trace map.
# OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:4318
# OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=kassa-api
